            <h2>Frontier Airlines – Accessible to All of America</h2>

            <p> <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/frontier-airlines.aspx"><b>Frontier Airlines</b></a> is one of the most popular airlines which operates on an ultra-low-cost carrier model in the United States of America charging a very low price for tickets and multiple optional add-on fees as per the preferences and requirements of the travellers aboard. The airline has been making air travel an accessible experience for many people of the country since it was first established thirty years ago on 8th February in the year 1944. The airlines commenced operations nearly five months later on 5th July of the same year thus putting a negligible gap between establishment and operations.</p>

            <p>A point of popularity for the airline has been its successful implementation of the ultra-low-cost model which allows travellers a far greater degree of autonomy than other standard options. The airline has a codeshare agreement with Volaris Airlines, another airline of the North American continent which follows the low-cost airlines model with most of its functions being carried out in Mexico.</p>

            <p>Frontier Airlines has a considerable network both within and outside the country and provides travel deals to a total of eighty – five destinations. These are spread all over its native country and Mexico in North America, some Caribbean Islands and Central America.</p>

